description.plain: Brenda Lee is an American singer, one of the leading pop singers of the 1950s and 1960s, nicknamed “Little Miss Dynamite” for her petite physique.

songs.lyrics:
27 ContributorsRockin’ Around The Christmas Tree Lyrics[Intro: Chorus]
Ahh-ahh-ahh

[Verse: Brenda Lee]
Rockin' around the Christmas tree
At the Christmas party hop
Mistletoe hung where you can see
Every couple tries to stop
Rockin' around the Christmas tree
Let the Christmas spirit ring
Later, we'll have some pumpkin pie
And we'll do some caroling

[Pre-Chorus: Brenda Lee, Chorus & Both]
You will get a sentimental feeling when you hear
Voices singing, "Let's be jolly (Ooo)
Deck the halls with boughs of holly!"

[Chorus: Brenda Lee]
Rockin' around the Christmas tree
Have a happy holiday
Everyone's dancing merrily
In the new old-fashioned way

[Saxophone Solo]
You might also like[Pre-Chorus: Brenda Lee, Chorus & Both]
You will get a sentimental feeling when you hear
Voices singing, "Let's be jolly (Ooo)
Deck the halls with boughs of holly!"

[Chorus: Brenda Lee & Chorus]
Rockin' around the Christmas tree
Have a happy holiday
Everyone's dancing merrily
In the new old fashioned way (Ahh)9Embed

My baby give me that special look
Sweet nothin's

Sweet nothin's
